A-Eng. HB 4134
1 (B) 0.9 percent for distribution in accordance with ORS 320.335 (3)(b); and
2 (C) 0.35 percent for distribution in accordance with ORS 320.335 (3)(c).
3 (b)(A) The tax must be computed on the total retail price, including all charges other than taxes,
4 paid by a person for occupancy of the transient lodging.
5 (B) The total retail price paid by a person for occupancy of transient lodging that is part of a
6 travel package may be determined by reasonable and verifiable standards from books and records
7 kept in the ordinary course of the transient lodging tax collector’s business.
8 (2) The tax imposed under this section becomes due when the occupancy of the transient lodging
9 with respect to which the tax is imposed ends.
10 (3)(a) The tax shall be collected by the transient lodging provider or transient lodging interme-
11 diary that collects the consideration charged for occupancy of the transient lodging, or a transient
12 lodging intermediary described in ORS 320.300 (12)(c), as applicable.
13 (b) The transient lodging tax collector may withhold a collection reimbursement charge of five
14 percent of the amount collected under this subsection.
15 (4) The tax imposed under this section is in addition to and not in lieu of any local transient
16 lodging tax.
