14 SECTION 3. ORS 320.303 is amended to read:
15 320.303. (1) A transient lodging tax collector shall, upon payment, provide to the person that
16 pays the consideration charged for occupancy of transient lodging an invoice, receipt or other sim-
17 ilar document that clearly sets forth the sum of all transient lodging taxes charged for the occu-
18 pancy of the transient lodging.
19 (2) The invoice, receipt or other similar document shall describe the portion of the tax
20 imposed at the rates set forth in ORS 320.305 (1)(a)(B) and (C) as a “nature conservation
21 fee.”
22 [(2)] (3) The invoice, receipt or other similar document may be in any form that the transient
23 lodging tax collector uses in the ordinary course of business.
